translations.Manage data within tables.\n\nWith this:
Manage data within tables.

With this app you are able to create your own tables with individual columns. You can start with a template or from scratch and add your wanted columns.
You can choose from the following column types:
- Text line or long text
- Link
- Number
- Progress bar
- Stars rating
- Yes/No tick
- Date and/or time

Share your tables with users and groups within your cloud.

Have a good time and manage whatever you want.

translations.The app will attempt to work out which c: The app will attempt to work out which columns in the data correspond to columns in the table. It tries three different ways to achieve this:
translations.First it checks the values of all column: First it checks the values of all columns in the first row of data to see if they match the titles of columns in the table.
translations.If any of the columns don't match it the: If any of the columns don't match it then tries the same approach but with the column ids.
translations.If either of those options match, the ap: If either of those options match, the app will assume the columns in the data are in the same order as the visible columns in the table and import them that way. There have to be two dummy columns for the row numbers and edit-button-column.
translations.The format for a date has to be like YYY: The format for a date must be YYYY-MM-DD, such as 2022-12-24.
translations.If you try to import by column order, se: If you try to import by column order, see the third point above. You need to add two dummy columns at the beginning.
translations.If you are on a Chrome browser, you have: If you are on a Chrome browser, you have to create a row first. Click on this newly created row and the insert process should run.
